      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/52/3",
      "text": [
        " : سُئِلَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ وَلَدِ اَلزِّنَا أَ يُشْتَرَى أَوْ يُبَاعُ أَوْ يُسْتَخْدَمُ قَالَ \"نَعَمْ إِلاَّ جَارِيَةً لَقِيطَةً فَإِنَّهَا لاَ تُشْتَرَى\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3530 - It is narrated from Hammad, from Al-Halabi, who said:\n\"Abu Abdullah (as), was asked about a child born out of adultery-can he be bought, sold, or used for service?\nImam (as) said: 'Yes, except for a foundling girl (abandoned by parents), as she cannot be bought.' \""
        ]
      }
    },
